A subquery is a query inside another SQL query.
It is used when you need the result of one query to be used in another.
It is written inside parentheses ().

Types of Query:

Root Query: Independent query.

Parent Query (or) Outer Query (or) Main Query:
The query which depends on any other query for its condition value.

Child Query (or) Inner Query (or) Sub Query:
Query within another query embedded in the WHERE clause of another SQL query.
The query which provides conditional values to its parent query.
Operators like =, <, >, >=, <=, IN, BETWEEN can be used.
Within the WHERE clause, up to 255 subqueries can be nested.


Syntax : 
SELECT column_name
FROM table_name
WHERE column_name expression_operator
(SELECT column_name FROM table_name WHERE ...);

example :
select emp id,empname,empsalary from emp where empsalary= (select max(empsalary) from emp);

